This category of Mitigations describes a range of actions aimed at promoting sustainable and clean energy sources, reducing greenhouse gas emissions, and improving energy efficiency. It includes strategies such as implementing renewable energy sources, adopting energy-efficient technologies, promoting clean energy manufacturing and deployment, and stricter regulations on emissions. The mitigations also focus on educating and raising awareness about energy conservation, providing incentives for energy-saving practices, and conducting audits to monitor energy consumption. Other measures include promoting sustainable production and consumption methods, using water-efficient appliances and fixtures, and optimizing energy management through automation and smart systems. Additionally, it involves enhancing energy assistance programs, improving access to backup energy sources, and supporting low-income households with financial assistance and education on energy-saving practices. The objective of these mitigations is to transition towards a sustainable and low-carbon energy system, reduce energy consumption, and promote clean and renewable energy sources for a green recovery.